On January 9, 2023, Calpine’s attendees Matt Barmack, Vice President, Market & Regulatory Analysis; Avis Kowalewski, Vice President, Government & Regulatory Affairs; Joe Greco, Director, Strategic Origination; and Emily Turkel, Analyst, Government & Regulatory Affairs met with Jaime Rose Gannon, advisor to President Alice Busching Reynolds, over Webex from approximately 3:30 p.m. to 4:00 p.m.

Calpine has requested and had been granted an ex parte Webex meeting on January 9, 2023, from approximately 3:30 p.m. to 4:00 p.m. with Jaime Rose Gannon, advisor to President Alice Busching Reynolds. The purpose of the meeting is to discuss constraints and opportunities for additional geothermal operational flexibility.  Calpine’s tentative list of attendees is:  Matt Barmack, Vice President, Market & Regulatory Analysis; Avis Kowalewski, Vice President, Government & Regulatory Affairs; Joe Greco, Director, Strategic Origination; and Emily Turkel, Analyst, Government & Regulatory Affairs

3de6ec85b234685308e80f4bdcfd8fb4.description: MARIN CLEAN ENERGY NOTICE OF WRITTEN EX PARTE COMMUNICATION Marin Clean Energy (“MCE”), notices of written ex parte communications On July 28, 2022 between 12:01 PM and 12:10 PM, MCE’s Associate General Counsel, Michael Callahan, sent emails containing a biomass-related article to all five CPUC Commissioners and several members of their advisory staff. They are as follows: Commissioner John Reynolds: Suzanne Cassaza, Chief of Staff and Legal Advisor; Pilar Manriquez, Deputy Chief of Staff; Maria Sotero, Advisor; Sasha Goldberg, Advisor; and Cait Pollock, Advisor. Commissioner Shiroma: Cheryl Wynn, Energy Advisor; Andrew Dugowson, Energy and Transportation Advisor; Kelsey Choing, Energy and Water Advisor; and Brianna Grant, Analyst. Commissioner Houck: Eileen Odell, Interim Chief of Staff and Water and Communications Policy Advisor; Kathleen Yip, Energy Advisor; Maryam Mozafari, Interim Energy Advisor; Adam Buchholz, Interim Energy Advisor; and Anna-Marie Madrigal, Associate-Governmental Program Analyst. Commissioner Rechtschaffen: Sean Simon, Chief of Staff; Yulia Schmidt, Advisor; Sandy Goldberg, Advisor; Simi Rose George, Advisor; Joanna Perez-Green, Advisor; and Karin Sung, Advisor. President Reynolds: Anand Durvasula, Michael Mullaney, Interim Communications and Transportation Advisor; Jason Reiger, Interim Legal and Policy Advisor; Vanessa Baldwin, Interim Legal and Policy Advisor; Rosie O’Hara, Interim Legal; and Policy Advisor; and KerryFleisher, Interim Energy Policy Advisor. The emails are attached below as Attachment 1 and the biomass-related article as Attachment 2.

b693bb5e0990a13034ca12c9f5fdb151.description: SUMMARY:  On October 30,2018, Steven Kelly, Policy Director for Independent Energy Producers Association (IEP), and Brian Cragg, outside counsel to IEP, met with Sandy Goldberg, advisor to Cmmr. Rechtschaffen, in San Francisco. Mr. Kelly reiterated the points made in IEP's comments on the 2018 Renewables Portfolio Standard (RPS) procurement plans, filed on September 21,2018. Mr. Kelly observed that the revised RPS procurement plans filed by load-serving entities in response to the enactment of Senate Bill 100 did not reveal a significant change in procurement and would not result in the procurement of new renewable energy resources needed by 2030. Mr. Kelly explained that to avoid a boom-or-bust cycle for procurement of renewable energy from new resources, the Commission should exercise the authority the Legislature granted it in Public Utilities Code Section 399.15(bX3) and increase the RPS requirement for LSEs above the statutory minimum. Mr. Cragg observed that an increased RPS level would also mesh with the state's efforts to reduce greenhouse gas emission levels by 2030. Mr. Kelly and Mr. Cragg also discussed the issues raised by proposals for a procurement entity. Written materials (attached to the notice) were used.

2b8a023089c6b3150a2a4ad9fb29a631.filed_by: The American Wind Energy Association California Caucus
2b8a023089c6b3150a2a4ad9fb29a631.description: SUMMARY:  On October 4, 2018, Brian Biering, Counsel, and Danielle Mills, Director, of of the the American Wind Energy Association (AWEA) California Caucus (ACC), and Johnny Casana of Pattern Energy, Scott Farris of EDP Renewables, and Virinder Singh of EDF Renewable Energy, as participating representative member companies, had a telephonic ex parte communication with Jennifer Kalafut and Ehren Seybert, advisors to Cmmr. Peterman. ACC members discussed integration between the Integrated Resource Planning and Renewable Portfolio Standard proceedings and recommended that the interaction between the procurement and transmission planning process needs to be a coordinated effort between the Commission and the California Independent System Operator with clear direction from both moving forward. ACC Members stressed the importance of timing in the current procurement cycle. ACC members also discussed the fleeting opportunity to obtain low-cost sources of renewable energy with the federal production tax credit (PTC) set to expire. ACC Members discussed the levelized cost of wind, both with and without the PTC, and how individual Load-Serving Entities reflect the value of PTC-eligible wind.
